<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Economy">Economy</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Beersheba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Economy">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:152px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG/150px-Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG" decoding="async" width="150" height="200" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG/225px-Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG/300px-Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG 2x" data-file-width="1200" data-file-height="1600" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Negev_Mall_Tower.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Negev Mall Tower</div></div></div>
<p>The largest employers in Beersheba are <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soroka_Medical_Center" title="Soroka Medical Center">Soroka Medical Center</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-100" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-100">&#91;97&#93;</a></sup> the municipality, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel_Defense_Forces" title="Israel Defense Forces">Israel Defense Forces</a> and Ben-Gurion University. A major <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel_Aerospace_Industries" title="Israel Aerospace Industries">Israel Aerospace Industries</a> complex is located in the main industrial zone, north of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Highway_60_(Israel)" class="mw-redirect" title="Highway 60 (Israel)">Highway 60</a>. Numerous electronics and chemical plants, including <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teva_Pharmaceutical_Industries" class="mw-redirect" title="Teva Pharmaceutical Industries">Teva Pharmaceutical Industries</a>, are located in and around the city.
</p><p>Beersheba is emerging as a high-tech center, with an emphasis on cyber security.<sup id="cite_ref-globes2_5-1" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-globes2-5">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> A large high-tech park is being built near the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Be%27er_Sheva_North_Railway_Station" class="mw-redirect" title="Be&#39;er Sheva North Railway Station">Be'er Sheva North Railway Station</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-autogenerated2_101-0" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-autogenerated2-101">&#91;98&#93;</a></sup> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deutsche_Telekom" title="Deutsche Telekom">Deutsche Telekom</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elbit_Systems" title="Elbit Systems">Elbit Systems</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EMC_Corporation" class="mw-redirect" title="EMC Corporation">EMC</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lockheed_Martin" title="Lockheed Martin">Lockheed Martin</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ness_Technologies" class="mw-redirect" title="Ness Technologies">Ness Technologies</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WeWork" title="WeWork">WeWork</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RAD_Data_Communications" title="RAD Data Communications">RAD Data Communications</a> have already opened facilities there, as has a cyberincubator run by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerusalem_Venture_Partners" title="Jerusalem Venture Partners">Jerusalem Venture Partners</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-102" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-102">&#91;99&#93;</a></sup> A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Science_park" title="Science park">Science park</a> funded by the RASHI-SACTA Foundation, Beersheba Municipality and private donors was completed in 2008.<sup id="cite_ref-autogenerated2_101-1" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-autogenerated2-101">&#91;98&#93;</a></sup> Another high-tech park is located north of the city near <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omer,_Israel" title="Omer, Israel">Omer</a>.
</p><p>An additional three industrial zones are located on the southeastern side of the city&#160;– Makhteshim, Emek Sara and Kiryat Yehudit&#160;– and a light industry zone between Kiryat Yehudit and the Old City.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Local_government">Local government</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Beersheba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Local government">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg/220px-PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="165" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg/330px-PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg/440px-PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2048" data-file-height="1536" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:PikiWiki_Israel_10420_court_house_in_beer_sheva.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Beersheba District Court</div></div></div>
<p>The Beersheba municipality was plagued for many years by an ineffectual leadership, political problems and poor financial planning. Since 2005, attention has been focused on developing parks and infrastructure. A new youth center opened in 2005, and a new cultural centre opened in 2008. In 2006, after many years of financial struggle, the municipality has achieved a balanced budget.<sup id="cite_ref-103" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-103">&#91;100&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The official emblem of the municipality of Beersheba depicts an <i>eshel</i> (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tamarix" title="Tamarix">tamarisk</a> tree), the tree planted by Abraham according to Genesis,<sup id="cite_ref-104" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-104">&#91;101&#93;</a></sup> and the observation tower connected to the municipality building.
</p><p>The mayor of Beersheba is <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruvik_Danilovich" title="Ruvik Danilovich">Ruvik Danilovich</a>, who was deputy mayor under <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yaakov_Turner" title="Yaakov Turner">Yaakov Turner</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-105" class="reference"><a href="Beersheba#cite_note-105">&#91;102&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
