<li id="cite_note-Musil-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Beersheba#cite_ref-Musil_25-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFAlois_Musil1908" class="citation book">Alois Musil (1908). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/stream/arabiapetraea00musigoog#page/n81/mode/2up"><i>Arabia Petraea</i></a>. <b>2</b>. Wien. p.&#160;66. <q>Bir es-Seba wächst von Tag zu Tag; heuer baut man bereits anstatt der Zelte stattliche Häuser, die eine schöne Straße vom Seräja zum Talbette bilden. Beim Regierungsgebäude hat man einen Garten angelegt und allerlei Bäume gesetzt, welche gewiß gut fortkommen werden, denn die wenigen vor zwei Jahren bei der Dampfmühle am Südostende der Straße gepflanzten Sträucher sind inzwischen stark gewachsen. Die rege Bautätigkeit verursacht auch hier eine rege Ausbeutung des Ruinenfeldes.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Arabia+Petraea&amp;rft.place=Wien&amp;rft.pages=66&amp;rft.date=1908&amp;rft.au=Alois+Musil&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Farabiapetraea00musigoog%23page%2Fn81%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABeersheba" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Robinson1908-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Beersheba#cite_ref-Robinson1908_26-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFGeorge_L._Robinson1908" class="citation journal">George L. Robinson (1908). "Beersheba Revisited". <i>The Biblical World</i>. <b>31</b> (5): 322+327–335. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="cs1-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1086%2F474045">10.1086/474045</a></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Biblical+World&amp;rft.atitle=Beersheba+Revisited&amp;rft.volume=31&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=322%2B327-335&amp;rft.date=1908&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1086%2F474045&amp;rft.au=George+L.+Robinson&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABeersheba" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Beersheba#cite_ref-27">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Abu Rabi'a (loc. cit.) names the other two as Palestinian Arabs <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nashashibi_clan" title="Nashashibi clan">Sa'id Effendi al-Nashashiby</a> and his assistant, Ragheb Effendi al-Nashashiby.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Accuracy_dispute#Disputed_statement" title="Wikipedia:Accuracy dispute"><span title="The material near this tag is possibly inaccurate or nonfactual. (December 2019)">dubious</span></a>&#32;<span class="metadata"> &#8211; <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:Beersheba#Don&#39;t_know_what_other_tag_to_use._Is_he_identical_with_Raghib_al-Nashashibi,_for_whom_there_is_a_WP_article?" title="Talk:Beersheba">discuss</a></span></i>&#93;</sup> However, Biger (Ottoman Town Planning in Late 19th
and early 20th Century Palestine, 3rd International Geography Symposium, 2013, 23–32) says that they were Turks educated in Germany.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Beersheba#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFGerdos,_Yehuda1985" class="citation book">Gerdos, Yehuda (1985). "Basis of Beersheba City Planning".  In Na'or, Mordechai (ed.). <i>Settlement of the Negev, 1900–1960</i> (in Hebrew). <a href="Jerusalem" title="Jerusalem">Jerusalem</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel" title="Israel">Israel</a>: Yad Yitzhak Ben-Zvi. pp.&#160;167–177.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Basis+of+Beersheba+City+Planning&amp;rft.btitle=Settlement+of+the+Negev%2C+1900%E2%80%931960&amp;rft.place=Jerusalem%2C+Israel&amp;rft.pages=167-177&amp;rft.pub=Yad+Yitzhak+Ben-Zvi&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.au=Gerdos%2C+Yehuda&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABeersheba" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
